{
  "stem": "1684.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In the meantime, I was in Auschwitz, and the ovens were burning day and night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In Birkenau, it was-- Birkenau it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The women's concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the ovens were going day and night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I met a cousin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "A cousin-- my-- my-- actually, she was not my cousin by birth.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Her fiance was a cousin who lived with us in Tarnow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he wanted to save himself, so he took a farmer of somebody, and he was supposed to take them out to-- to his house.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "In the meantime, he had the money, and he took him to the Gestapo, so he was killed, the cousin of mine.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she has fiance.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was taken from another town where she lived with her parents.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from [NON-ENGLISH]-- not from [NON-ENGLISH], from a town next to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were all gassed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she was all by herself.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, she was all by herself, and then she saw my name on-- on the list-- you know, she got to see the list-- she said to me, oh, I'm your cousin.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, oh, yeah, you're Hania Viener, I only heard about her, but I didn't know her.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when they came afterwards, to pick us out, to call our name, I said to the [NON-ENGLISH] there, who took us out, he was-- I was telling him, in German, I met a cousin, can she go with me?",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And not that I knew that it's safe, but somehow I wanted to stay with her, and he said, OK.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she went with me to Brunnlitz, and she lived through the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she has two sons-- a son and a daughter, and they have, between the two, they have 11 grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But she is very sick.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
